---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting"
  description="Consulting, workshops and talks on AI literacy, Human-AI Interaction and psychologically informed AI adoption."
>
  <section class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Consulting</p>
        <h1>
          Consulting, workshops and talks on AI literacy, Human-AI Interaction and the
          psychology of working with AI.
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        Research-informed support for organizations, teams and institutions that need to
        understand the human side of AI adoption.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="two-column">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Prompted Psyche treats AI adoption as a human and organizational question, not
          only a technical rollout. The work focuses on judgment, trust, communication,
          responsibility and the everyday psychology of using generative tools.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is to help people and teams develop clearer language, better boundaries
          and more thoughtful workflows for working with AI in real contexts.
        </p>

        <div class="panel">
          <h2>What this is not</h2>
          <p>
            This is not legal advice, clinical advice or a tool demo focused only on
            prompts. The focus is the human side of AI use: judgment, trust, communication,
            responsibility and work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="panel">
          <h3>What I help with</h3>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>AI literacy for organizations</li>
            <li>Human-AI workflows</li>
            <li>Trust and decision-making with AI</li>
            <li>Responsible use of generative AI</li>
            <li>AI in communication and creative work</li>
            <li>Psychological and cultural consequences of AI adoption</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="panel">
          <h3>Best fit</h3>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>Leadership teams</li>
            <li>Communication / marketing / content teams</li>
            <li>HR / L&amp;D</li>
            <li>Education and cultural institutions</li>
            <li>Creative teams</li>
            <li>Organizations preparing internal AI guidelines</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="panel">
          <h3>Formats</h3>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>Expert briefing</li>
            <li>Workshop</li>
            <li>Advisory session</li>
            <li>Talk / lecture</li>
            <li>Research-informed review</li>
            <li>Internal AI use principles session</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="panel">
          <h3>How a session can work</h3>
          <ol class="plain-list">
            <li>Context</li>
            <li>Risks and use cases</li>
            <li>Human-AI workflow</li>
            <li>Practical principles</li>
            <li>Next steps</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="contact-band" aria-labelledby="consulting-contact-title">
      <p class="small-label" id="consulting-contact-title">Contact</p>
      <p>
        For consulting, talks or workshops, send a concise note with context, timeline and
        the kind of support you are looking for.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
